      "body": "> Also there is GO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway, 10 IEA annotations, no EXP. @sjm41 I think this too should be 'merged' into (obsolete with consider) GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway or GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Do you agree?\n\n@raymond91125  Yes, I'd suggest that term is merged into its parent GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Thanks.\n\nI'll note that the 10 IEA annotations are all by CGD, based on evidence from [PomBase:SPAC4G9.12](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPAC4G9.12) or [PomBase:SPBC660.16](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPBC660.16).\nLooking at those records in PomBase, they are annotated with a different BP \"pentose-phosphate shunt, oxidative branch (GO:0009051)\". So CGD may want to change those annotations anyway. (I don't know who the CGD contact is.)",
